article.headline: Bowling Green 65, South Alabama 64
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Ryne Hamblet's layup as time ran out lifted Bowling Green to a 65-64 victory over South Alabama on Saturday. The Jaguars (4-2) pulled ahead 64-63 on a pair of free throws by Brandon Davis with nine seconds left, but Darryl Clements found Hamblet for the easy basket as the clock ran out. The Falcons (2-2) took a 17-7 lead on Erik Marschall's jumper with 11:56 left in the first half, but South Alabama pulled to 30-29 on a pair of Davis free throws to end the period. The game stayed tight through the second half. Martin Samarco led the Falcons with 23 points, while Matt Lefeld added 12 and Marschall 10. Hamblet's winning basket gave him four points. Demetric Bennett had 19 points for the Jaguars, Davis added 14 and Daon Merritt 10.
